## Your job

For each person item where vault-match produced a hit
(``match != null``), read the existing vault page in full
(frontmatter + body) and write a **merged item** whose
``definition`` (and ``bio`` if used) integrates the existing
page's content with the new info this run extracted.

You MUST:

- **Preserve** the existing page's biographical claims and
  affiliations unless this run's source explicitly contradicts
  them. The existing page may carry hand-authored notes the
  user values; do not strip them.
- Produce a ``rationale`` (1-3 sentences) describing what new
  facts this run contributes (e.g. an additional role, a new
  affiliation period, a new domain of work). If none, set
  ``new_info_present: false`` and say so plainly.
- Produce an ``existing_summary`` (1 line) describing what the
  existing page said before merging.
- Treat name collisions carefully — two people share names. If
  the existing page's role/affiliation/domain clearly identifies
  a different person, set ``new_info_present: true`` and produce
  a ``merged_item`` matching this run's extracted item verbatim,
  with a rationale flagging the collision so the operator can
  rename one of the pages.

