## Writing Output

Write the merge output by invoking ``loom output`` via
execute_bash. DO NOT use ``fs_write`` directly.

Output target:

    {{ task.output_path }}

### 1. Initialize

    {{ vars.loom_sh }} output init {{ run.workdir }} --task {{ task.id }}

### 2. Emit one ``merges`` entry per matched item

For each matched person above (skip none — every match must
appear in ``merges``):

    {{ vars.loom_sh }} output add {{ run.workdir }} --task {{ task.id }} \
        --set merges.<i>.name='<person name>' \
        --set merges.<i>.vault_path='<relative vault path from match>' \
        --set merges.<i>.merged_item.name='<person name>' \
        --set merges.<i>.merged_item.role='<role>' \
        --set merges.<i>.merged_item.definition='<integrated definition>' \
        --set merges.<i>.merged_item.source_quote='<this run source_quote or empty>' \
        --set merges.<i>.rationale='<1-3 sentences: what new info this run contributes>' \
        --set merges.<i>.existing_summary='<1-line summary of prior page>' \
        --set merges.<i>.new_info_present=<true|false>

Increment ``<i>`` per merged item (0, 1, 2, ...).

If no items matched (``merges`` is empty), seed the array:

    {{ vars.loom_sh }} output add {{ run.workdir }} --task {{ task.id }} --set merges='[]'
